-- Nigeria's Diamond Bank sees $550 mln share sale this year - CEO 
-- By Chijioke Ohuocha
-- Mon Apr 14, 2014 12:44PM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, April 14 (Reuters) - Nigeria's Diamond Bank <DIAMONB.LG> expects to tap equity markets before the end of the year to raise up to $550 million to shore up its capital base, its chief executive said on Monday.

"We are over 17 percent capital adequacy ... but still looking to raise more capital. We will look at the equity market before the end of the year," Otti told an analyst conference call.